                <p>consisting of 23 leaves, some of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 1, 4—6, 12—15, 17—21, and 23.</p>
                <gap reason="lacuna">
                  <desc>As at present bound, there are lacunae after foll. 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 10, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 18, and 22.</desc>
                </gap>
                <!--are we doing lacunae correctly?-->
                <signatures>
                  The quires are signed with letters, and were originally at least 22 in number (fol 7 a, ܛ; fol. 21 a, ܟܒ); but not a single one is now perfect.
                  <!--TEI would also allow individual listed items for the collation but this is not necessary perhaps-->
                </signatures>
                
                <!--it would be good to have Lacuna  and restorations be separate tags, perhaps-->
              </condition>
            </supportDesc>
            <layoutDesc>
              <layout columns="0 2" writtenLines="34 38">
                <locus from="1" to="22"></locus>
                <p> Each page is divided into two columns, of from 34 to 38 lines</p>
