            </layoutDesc>
          </objectDesc>
          <handDesc>
            <handNote scope="major" script="not specified" medium="not specified">
              <!--not sure how to do multiple inks here-->
              <desc>This volume is written in a good, current hand of the vith or viith cent.</desc>
            </handNote>
          </handDesc>
          <additions>
            <list>
              <item>
                <label>Marginalia</label>
                <p>Whether the <locus from="23b">fly-leaf, fol. 23,</locus> which is much stained and torn, really belongs to this manuscript, is doubtful. On the recto, there are three entries of deaths, all of which have been purposely effaced. The first is that of a bishop. In the third, the words <quote>ܘܡܬܝܢ ܕܛܝܝ̈ܐ</quote> are still legible, showing that these entries belong to the third cent, of the <date>Hijra, A.D. 815—912.</date></p>
              </item>
            </list>
          </additions>    
